title: Google\Cloud\BigQuery\DataExchange\V1beta1\Listing
name: Listing
description:
A listing is what gets published into a data exchange that a subscriber can subscribe to. It contains a reference to the data source along with descriptive information that will help subscribers find and subscribe the data.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.bigquery.dataexchange.v1beta1.Listing

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.bigquery_dataset
params.description: Required. Shared dataset i.e. BigQuery dataset source.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The resource name of the listing. e.g. projects/myproject/locations/US/dataExchanges/123/listings/456

params.name: data.display_name
params.description: Required. Human-readable display name of the listing. The display name must contain only Unicode letters, numbers (0-9), underscores (_), dashes (-), spaces ( ), ampersands (&) and can't start or end with spaces. Default value is an empty string. Max length: 63 bytes.

params.name: data.description
params.description: Optional. Short description of the listing. The description must not contain Unicode non-characters and C0 and C1 control codes except tabs (HT), new lines (LF), carriage returns (CR), and page breaks (FF). Default value is an empty string. Max length: 2000 bytes.

params.name: data.primary_contact
params.description: Optional. Email or URL of the primary point of contact of the listing. Max Length: 1000 bytes.

params.name: data.documentation
params.description: Optional. Documentation describing the listing.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. Current state of the listing.

params.name: data.icon
params.description: Optional. Base64 encoded image representing the listing. Max Size: 3.0MiB Expected image dimensions are 512x512 pixels, however the API only performs validation on size of the encoded data. Note: For byte fields, the contents of the field are base64-encoded (which increases the size of the data by 33-36%) when using JSON on the wire.

params.name: data.data_provider
params.description: Optional. Details of the data provider who owns the source data.

params.name: data.categories
params.description: Optional. Categories of the listing. Up to two categories are allowed.

params.name: data.publisher
params.description: Optional. Details of the publisher who owns the listing and who can share the source data.

params.name: data.request_access
params.description: Optional. Email or URL of the request access of the listing. Subscribers can use this reference to request access. Max Length: 1000 bytes.
